	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Abashi/Brad, this following paragraph disturbs me:<BR>
<BR>
&quot;You hereby grant us permission to download Game-related files to you. You also grant us<BR>
permission to access, extract and upload (i) Game-related data from the Everquest<BR>
program folder as part of the patching process and (ii) data relating to any actively<BR>
running program that we, in our reasonable discretion, determine interferes with the proper<BR>
operation of EverQuest.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
I know you can't trust everyone, but I take that as almost an insult that you are going to be rummaging through my PC, even out of good intentions.<BR>
<BR>
I would highly recommend you put in place a log of what you scan so WE can see what processes YOU are scanning and especially what files you &quot;extract and upload&quot;. I keep things on my computer which you have no business being in and it would greatly upset me if I found you had yanked up my bank account or something.<BR>
I tend to be a lurker on these posts but having been in the programming community for the last 8 years has made me more than a bit paranoid about letting ANYONE have random access to my PC.<BR>
<BR>
Thanks for your time<BR>
-Mike
				</font>
			</td>

